    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Public Presidential Sentiment\"\nsubtitle: \"Approval, economic sentiment, and media sentiment by administration — 1999 to present\"\n---\n\n\n\nThis report measures three different dimensions of public sentiment during\neach presidential administration from 1999 to the present:\n\n1. **Political approval** — aggregate Gallup approval averages by administration\n   (hand-curated; polling APIs aren't free for full history).\n2. **Economic sentiment** — University of Michigan Consumer Sentiment Index\n   (`UMCSENT`, monthly, via FRED — public-domain; auto-refreshed daily).\n3. **Media sentiment** — GDELT Doc 2.0 daily average-tone of US-presidency\n   English-language news (CC-BY-NC; 2017-present only).\n4. **Society radar** — editorial six-aspect summary (Public Safety, Economy,\n   Health, Prosperity, Happiness, Peace) on a −10/+10 scale per\n   administration.\n\n::: {.callout-important appearance=\"simple\"}\nNone of these measures capture presidents directly — they capture **public\nresponse** during a period that includes the president plus every other\ninfluence on public mood (wars, pandemics, the business cycle, global shocks,\nmedia environment). Treat these as descriptive, not causal. See\n[Methodology](about.qmd) for the full caveats.\n:::\n\n## Baselines\n\nAcross the administrations displayed (Clinton partial → Trump II):\n\n- **UMCSENT baseline:** 82.6 (mean of monthly observations\n  in the 1999-to-present window that are tagged to a displayed admin).\n- **Gallup baseline:** 47.1% (mean of the five completed\n  admins' term-average approvals).\n\nNumbers further right of zero in the \"vs baseline\" columns mean **above**\nthe cross-administration average; left of zero means **below**.\n\n## Summary by administration {#summary}\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"reactable html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-fb559c538b50ad8132b4\" style=\"width:auto;height:auto;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-fb559c538b50ad8132b4\">{\"x\":{\"tag\":{\"name\":\"Reactable\",\"attribs\":{\"data\":{\"president\":[\"Bill Clinton\",\"George W. Bush\",\"Barack Obama\",\"Donald Trump (1st term)\",\"Joe Biden\",\"Donald Trump (2nd term) *\"],\"party\":[\"Democratic\",\"Republican\",\"Democratic\",\"Republican\",\"Democratic\",\"Republican\"],\"gallup_avg\":[55.1,49.4,47.9,41,42.2,\"NA\"],\"gallup_vs_baseline\":[8,2.3,0.8,-6.1,-4.9,\"NA\"],\"umcsent_avg\":[106.2,85.5,79.2,92.8,68.5,56.3],\"umcsent_vs_baseline\":[23.6,2.9,-3.4,10.2,-14.1,-26.3]},\"columns\":[{\"id\":\"president\",\"name\":\"President\",\"type\":\"character\",\"minWidth\":180},{\"id\":\"party\",\"name\":\"Party\",\"type\":\"character\",\"cell\":[{\"name\":\"span\",\"attribs\":{\"style\":{\"display\":\"inline-block\",\"padding\":\"2px 8px\",\"border-radius\":\"3px\",\"font-size\":\"0.72rem\",\"font-weight\":\"600\",\"color\":\"#fff\",\"background\":\"#2a6f97\"}},\"children\":[\"DEMOCRATIC\"]},{\"name\":\"span\",\"attribs\":{\"style\":{\"display\":\"inline-block\",\"padding\":\"2px 8px\",\"border-radius\":\"3px\",\"font-size\":\"0.72rem\",\"font-weight\":\"600\",\"color\":\"#fff\",\"background\":\"#bc4749\"}},\"children\":[\"REPUBLICAN\"]},{\"name\":\"span\",\"attribs\":{\"style\":{\"display\":\"inline-block\",\"padding\":\"2px 8px\",\"border-radius\":\"3px\",\"font-size\":\"0.72rem\",\"font-weight\":\"600\",\"color\":\"#fff\",\"background\":\"#2a6f97\"}},\"children\":[\"DEMOCRATIC\"]},{\"name\":\"span\",\"attribs\":{\"style\":{\"display\":\"inline-block\",\"padding\":\"2px 8px\",\"border-radius\":\"3px\",\"font-size\":\"0.72rem\",\"font-weight\":\"600\",\"color\":\"#fff\",\"background\":\"#bc4749\"}},\"children\":[\"REPUBLICAN\"]},{\"name\":\"span\",\"attribs\":{\"style\":{\"display\":\"inline-block\",\"padding\":\"2px 8px\",\"border-radius\":\"3px\",\"font-size\":\"0.72rem\",\"font-weight\":\"600\",\"color\":\"#fff\",\"background\":\"#2a6f97\"}},\"children\":[\"DEMOCRATIC\"]},{\"name\":\"span\",\"attribs\":{\"style\":{\"display\":\"inline-block\",\"padding\":\"2px 8px\",\"border-radius\":\"3px\",\"font-size\":\"0.72rem\",\"font-weight\":\"600\",\"color\":\"#fff\",\"background\":\"#bc4749\"}},\"children\":[\"REPUBLICAN\"]}],\"html\":true,\"minWidth\":110},{\"id\":\"gallup_avg\",\"name\":\"Gallup avg (%)\",\"type\":\"numeric\",\"format\":{\"cell\":{\"suffix\":\"%\",\"digits\":1},\"aggregated\":{\"suffix\":\"%\",\"digits\":1}}},{\"id\":\"gallup_vs_baseline\",\"name\":\"vs baseline\",\"type\":\"numeric\",\"format\":{\"cell\":{\"digits\":1},\"aggregated\":{\"digits\":1}},\"style\":[{\"color\":\"#2f9e44\",\"fontWeight\":600},{\"color\":\"#2f9e44\",\"fontWeight\":600},{\"color\":\"#2f9e44\",\"fontWeight\":600},{\"color\":\"#bc4749\",\"fontWeight\":600},{\"color\":\"#bc4749\",\"fontWeight\":600},[]]},{\"id\":\"umcsent_avg\",\"name\":\"UMCSENT avg\",\"type\":\"numeric\",\"format\":{\"cell\":{\"digits\":1},\"aggregated\":{\"digits\":1}}},{\"id\":\"umcsent_vs_baseline\",\"name\":\"vs baseline\",\"type\":\"numeric\",\"format\":{\"cell\":{\"digits\":1},\"aggregated\":{\"digits\":1}},\"style\":[{\"color\":\"#2f9e44\",\"fontWeight\":600},{\"color\":\"#2f9e44\",\"fontWeight\":600},{\"color\":\"#bc4749\",\"fontWeight\":600},{\"color\":\"#2f9e44\",\"fontWeight\":600},{\"color\":\"#bc4749\",\"fontWeight\":600},{\"color\":\"#bc4749\",\"fontWeight\":600}]}],\"highlight\":true,\"striped\":true,\"compact\":true,\"theme\":{\"borderColor\":\"#dee2e6\"},\"dataKey\":\"73717e295e567fa12df842547465ff6a\"},\"children\":[]},\"class\":\"reactR_markup\"},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Political approval vs economic sentiment {#combined}\n\nTwo different things the two measures capture: approval is *about the president*,\nUMCSENT is *about the economy the public perceives*. They often move together\nbut don't have to.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"echarts4r html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-30b75e1634768778705e\" style=\"width:100%;height:500px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-30b75e1634768778705e\">{\"x\":{\"theme\":\"custom\",\"tl\":false,\"draw\":true,\"renderer\":\"canvas\",\"events\":[],\"buttons\":[],\"opts\":{\"yAxis\":[{\"show\":true,\"name\":\"Approval (%)\",\"axisLabel\":{\"formatter\":\"{value}%\"},\"max\":80},{\"type\":\"value\",\"name\":\"UMCSENT\",\"position\":\"right\",\"max\":120}],\"xAxis\":[{\"data\":[\"Clinton\",\"Bush (43)\",\"Obama\",\"Trump I\",\"Biden\",\"Trump II*\"],\"type\":\"category\",\"boundaryGap\":true}],\"legend\":{\"data\":[\"Gallup approval avg (%)\",\"UMCSENT avg\"],\"show\":true,\"type\":\"plain\",\"top\":24},\"series\":[{\"data\":[{\"value\":[\"Clinton\",\"55.1\"]},{\"value\":[\"Bush (43)\",\"49.4\"]},{\"value\":[\"Obama\",\"47.9\"]},{\"value\":[\"Trump I\",\"41.0\"]},{\"value\":[\"Biden\",\"42.2\"]},{\"value\":[\"Trump II*\",null]}],\"name\":\"Gallup approval avg (%)\",\"type\":\"bar\",\"yAxisIndex\":0,\"xAxisIndex\":0,\"coordinateSystem\":\"cartesian2d\",\"itemStyle\":{\"color\":\"function(p){ var c=[\\\"#2a6f97\\\",\\\"#bc4749\\\",\\\"#2a6f97\\\",\\\"#bc4749\\\",\\\"#2a6f97\\\",\\\"#bc4749\\\"]; return c[p.dataIndex]; }\"}},{\"data\":[{\"value\":[\"Clinton\",\"106.2\"]},{\"value\":[\"Bush (43)\",\" 85.5\"]},{\"value\":[\"Obama\",\" 79.2\"]},{\"value\":[\"Trump I\",\" 92.8\"]},{\"value\":[\"Biden\",\" 68.5\"]},{\"value\":[\"Trump II*\",\" 56.3\"]}],\"name\":\"UMCSENT avg\",\"type\":\"bar\",\"yAxisIndex\":1,\"xAxisIndex\":0,\"coordinateSystem\":\"cartesian2d\",\"itemStyle\":{\"color\":\"#6a4c93\"},\"barGap\":\"20%\"}],\"tooltip\":{\"trigger\":\"axis\",\"valueFormatter\":\"function(v){ return typeof v==='number' ? v.toFixed(1) : v; }\"},\"title\":[{\"left\":\"center\",\"text\":\"Gallup approval (bars) vs UMCSENT (overlay)\",\"subtext\":\"Two separate measures of public mood; dual y-axes\"}]},\"dispose\":true,\"theme2\":true,\"customTheme\":\"{\\n  \\\"color\\\": [\\\"#2a6f97\\\",\\\"#e07a5f\\\",\\\"#bc4749\\\",\\\"#6a4c93\\\",\\\"#2f9e44\\\",\\\"#f2c14e\\\",\\\"#1d3557\\\",\\\"#6c757d\\\"],\\n  \\\"backgroundColor\\\": \\\"transparent\\\",\\n  \\\"textStyle\\\": { \\\"fontFamily\\\": \\\"system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, sans-serif\\\" },\\n  \\\"title\\\": { \\\"textStyle\\\": { \\\"fontWeight\\\": \\\"600\\\" } },\\n  \\\"legend\\\": { \\\"textStyle\\\": { \\\"color\\\": \\\"#495057\\\" } },\\n  \\\"grid\\\": { \\\"containLabel\\\": true, \\\"left\\\": 48, \\\"right\\\": 24, \\\"top\\\": 56, \\\"bottom\\\": 40 },\\n  \\\"xAxis\\\": { \\\"axisLine\\\": { \\\"lineStyle\\\": { \\\"color\\\": \\\"#adb5bd\\\" } } },\\n  \\\"yAxis\\\": { \\\"splitLine\\\": { \\\"lineStyle\\\": { \\\"color\\\": \\\"#e9ecef\\\" } } }\\n}\",\"theme_name\":\"econ\"},\"evals\":[\"opts.series.0.itemStyle.color\",\"opts.tooltip.valueFormatter\"],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Where to go next {#next}\n\n- **[Political Approval →](approval.qmd)** — Gallup per-admin averages, min/max volatility, exit vs. peak comparison.\n- **[Economic Sentiment →](economic.qmd)** — UMCSENT timeline shaded by administration, world events overlay, per-admin averages vs long-run baseline.\n- **[Media Sentiment →](media.qmd)** — GDELT-derived average-tone timeline, per-admin tone averages, coverage begins 2017.\n- **[Society Radar →](society.qmd)** — six-aspect radar chart on a −10/+10 scale per administration (editorial).\n- **[Methodology →](about.qmd)** — source provenance, why \"sentiment toward an administration\" is imprecise, caveats.\n",
